---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Wrapper from "@/components/fundations/containers/Wrapper.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <Wrapper variant="standard" class="py-16 lg:py-24">
    <header
      class="min-h-[50vh] flex flex-col justify-center pb-16"
    >
      <h1
        class="text-6xl sm:text-7xl md:text-8xl lg:text-[10rem] font-bold leading-[0.85] tracking-tighter uppercase mb-3"
      >
        Just fucking<br />use Astro
      </h1>
      <p
        class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl leading-snug max-w-2xl mb-3 text-black/70 dark:text-white/70"
      >
        (Unless you're building an actual app, you sweet, fragile,
        over-engineering dipshit motherfucker.)
      </p>
      <p
        class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-black/60 dark:text-white/60 border-l-2 border-current pl-4 max-w-xl"
      >
        This rant was written by <a
          href="https://michaelandreuzza.com/"
          class="underline hover:opacity-60">Michael Andreuzza</a
        > the motherfucker who made this fucking rant fucking possible when he had
        nothing to do.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        <strong class="font-semibold"
          >Most sites are content plus a few interactive bits.</strong
        ><br />
        If you're shipping a full SPA for a fucking marketing site, you're not "modern."
        You're a goddamn irresponsible jackass, lazy as shit with architecture, and
        actively making the web a worse fucking shithole for everyone. Fuck you.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tight uppercase mb-4"
      >
        What the fuck is this shit?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        This is a public service announcement for braindead dumbass
        motherfucking developers still building websites like it's 2012 <em
          >or</em
        > 2022 and acting proud of it like they invented sliced fucking bread, you
        absolute morons.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-3">
        You've got two equally stupid fucking religions:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="max-w-3xl mb-4 space-y-4"
      >
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="font-semibold">"No frameworks ever."</strong> Congrats,
          you fucking idiot, you rebuilt a worse CMS with worse routing, worse builds,
          and zero goddamn guardrails. Your shitty site is one junior dev away from
          collapsing into an unreadable pile of HTML sadness, tears, and your own
          fucking incompetence, dipshit.
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="font-semibold">"SPA for everything."</strong> Congrats,
          you pretentious motherfucker, you shipped hundreds of kilobytes of JavaScript
          bullshit to render a headline, three buttons, and your fragile fucking
          ego. Your users didn't consent to running your frontend thesis in their
          browser, you selfish piece of shit asshole.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Astro exists because most of the goddamn web is:
      </p>
      <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base"
        >
          fucking pages
        </li>
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base"
        >
          fucking content
        </li>
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base"
        >
          fucking navigation
        </li>
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base"
        >
          fucking forms
        </li>
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base"
        >
          a couple fucking interactive widgets
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        Not a goddamn desktop application duct-taped into a browser tab with
        delusions of grandeur, you delusional assclown.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tight uppercase mb-4"
      >
        Why Astro instead of "pure HTML"?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        Because "pure HTML" at scale is a fucking lie you tell yourself until
        the site hits page 37 and everything quietly catches fire and burns down
        around you like your pathetic career, motherfucker.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Then this shit happens, asshole:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="max-w-3xl mb-4 space-y-4"
      >
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          you copy and paste layouts like it's 2009 and you've learned
          absolutely fucking nothing, you braindead bastard
        </li>
        <li class="py-4 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          your "tiny bit of JS" becomes a cursed spaghetti altar of suffering
          and bullshit
        </li>
        <li class="py-4 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          content turns into an untyped clusterfuck no one fucking understands
        </li>
        <li class="py-4 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          the build process becomes duct tape, shell scripts, prayers, and
          eventual fucking alcoholism because of your incompetence
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        Astro gives you structure without forcing you into "everything must be
        client-side or you're a fucking coward," you spineless shit.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You get, motherfucker:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="max-w-3xl mb-4 space-y-4"
      >
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          components without joining a goddamn JS framework cult like a
          brainwashed idiot
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          actual layouts instead of copy-paste hell, dumbass
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          sane file-based routing that doesn't make you want to fucking scream
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          typed content collections so you stop shipping broken frontmatter like
          a fucking amateur piece of shit
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          the ability to use React, Vue, Svelte, or whatever the fuck <em
            >only</em
          > when needed
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold leading-snug max-w-3xl">
        And yes, this is still true in December 2025: Astro ships zero
        client-side JavaScript by default. No tricks. No asterisks. No bullshit
        hydration tax. Nothing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tight uppercase mb-4"
      >
        Why not just use React?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-4">
        Because React is great. For apps, dipshit.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        Most websites are not fucking apps, no matter how much you desperately
        want them to be, you delusional motherfucker.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">If your site is:</p>
      <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base font-medium"
        >
          marketing pages
        </li>
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base font-medium"
        >
          docs
        </li>
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base font-medium"
        >
          a blog
        </li>
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base font-medium"
        >
          landing pages
        </li>
        <li
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 text-sm sm:text-base font-medium"
        >
          ecommerce front
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        …then shipping a full SPA is like bringing a fucking forklift to carry a
        motherfucking sandwich, then congratulating yourself for "scalability"
        and "best practices," you insufferable jackass.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        Astro is the "HTML-first, JS-when-needed" workflow that SPA developers <em
          >say</em
        > they follow and then immediately ignore like the lying motherfucking bastards
        they are.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tight uppercase mb-4"
      >
        Islands Architecture
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        Here's the mental model. Pay the fuck attention, dipshit motherfucker.
      </p>
      <p class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold leading-tight max-w-2xl mb-4">
        Your page is static by default. Interactivity is the exception, not the
        fucking rule.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-md mb-4">
        <div
          class="text-center"
        >
          <p class="text-xs text-black/60 dark:text-white/60 mb-1">Carousel?</p>
          <p class="font-bold">Island</p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="text-center"
        >
          <p class="text-xs text-black/60 dark:text-white/60 mb-1">Pricing toggle?</p>
          <p class="font-bold">Island</p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="text-center"
        >
          <p class="text-xs text-black/60 dark:text-white/60 mb-1">Search?</p>
          <p class="font-bold">Island</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        Everything else stays server-rendered, boring, fast, and quiet — like a
        well-behaved website that respects its users.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        That fucking means:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="max-w-3xl mb-4 space-y-4"
      >
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          dramatically less JavaScript shipped to innocent users who didn't ask
          for your bullshit
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          fewer hydration nightmares that wake your dumbass up at 3am
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          fewer "why did this fucking re-render?" panic attacks and Slack
          meltdowns
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          a page that works immediately instead of after a JS warm-up ritual
          from hell that you created, asshole
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        You don't need to hydrate the fucking world, you absolute moron. You
        need to hydrate the <em>one</em> damn widget and leave the rest the fuck
        alone, jackass.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tight uppercase mb-4"
      >
        When to use Astro
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Just fucking use Astro when:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="max-w-3xl mb-4 space-y-4"
      >
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          your site is mostly content with some UI sprinkled on top, dumbass
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          SEO actually matters and isn't just bullshit buzzwords in your shitty
          deck
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          you want components without paying a stupid fucking SPA performance
          tax
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          you want React or Svelte only where it makes sense, not everywhere
          like a goddamn lunatic
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          your interactivity is localized instead of infecting the whole goddamn
          page like a fucking virus
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          you want a site that doesn't turn into a maintenance nightmare at 50+
          pages because you're too stupid to plan ahead
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        If you're thinking "but I can do that with vanilla JS", yes, and you can
        also eat soup with a fucking fork, you masochistic dipshit. Stop
        pretending that suffering equals skill, you self-righteous martyr
        asshole.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tight uppercase mb-4"
      >
        When NOT to use Astro
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Astro is not your magic wand if you're building:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="max-w-3xl mb-4 space-y-4"
      >
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          a heavy client-side app with shared state everywhere, jackass
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          real-time collaborative tools for fuck's sake
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          interfaces where literally everything is interactive all the fucking
          damn time
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          complex offline-first behavior that you'll probably fuck up anyway
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        If your UI is basically a constantly running program, stop cosplaying as
        a website like a fucking poser and just fucking use:
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
        <span
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 font-bold"
          >React / Next</span
        >
        <span
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 font-bold"
          >SvelteKit</span
        >
        <span
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 font-bold"
          >Remix</span
        >
        <span
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-black/5 dark:bg-white/10 font-bold"
          >Whatever works</span
        >
      </div>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        Astro is for sites that behave like websites, with selective "app"
        bullshit only where it belongs.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tight uppercase mb-4"
      >
        "But what about bloat?"
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        If you use Astro correctly, it <strong class="font-semibold"
          >does not ship what you don't use</strong
        >. That's the whole fucking point, genius. Are you fucking stupid?
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        If your Astro site ships 500KB of JavaScript, congratulations: you
        ignored the entire goddamn philosophy and rebuilt a SPA like a complete
        fucking idiot. You dumb motherfucker.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        That's not Astro's fault, dumbass. That's you being addicted to
        unnecessary complexity like it's fucking heroin. Get help, asshole.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tight uppercase mb-4"
      >
        The real problem
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        The real problem is developers who can't evaluate the fucking job and
        treat tool choice like a personality trait or a religion. You're the
        fucking problem, asshole.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Pick based on reality, not your pathetic feelings:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="max-w-3xl mb-4 space-y-4"
      >
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Content-heavy with selective interactivity? <strong
            class="font-semibold">Astro, dipshit.</strong>
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Highly interactive, stateful client app? <strong class="font-semibold"
            >React/Next/whatever, asshole.</strong>
        </li>
        <li class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Somewhere in between? <strong class="font-semibold"
            >Think for five goddamn seconds before copy-pasting last year's
            architecture.</strong>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        Stop treating tools like identity, you insecure motherfucker. It's
        engineering. Act like a goddamn professional for once in your worthless
        career.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2
        class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tighter uppercase mb-4"
      >
        Now go ship something fast
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-3">
        If you're building a mostly-content website and still reaching for a
        full SPA like a fucking amateur: you're not being advanced, dipshit.
        You're being lazy, insecure, and shit at trade-offs like the incompetent
        motherfucker you are.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        Go build something that loads fast, ships less JavaScript, and doesn't
        actively hate your users, you piece of shit. Now fuck off and code.
      </p>
    </section>

    <footer class="mt-12">
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-3">
        <strong class="font-semibold"
          >Also: if you want the fucking vibe, these were the obvious goddamn
          inspirations, you curious bastard:</strong
        >
      </p>
      <ul
        class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4"
      >
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://motherfuckingwebsite.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-sm hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity underline"
            >motherfuckingwebsite.com</a
          >
          <span class="text-sm text-black/60 dark:text-white/60"> — fucking classic</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://justfuckingusetailwind.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-sm hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity underline"
            >justfuckingusetailwind.com</a
          >
          <span class="text-sm text-black/60 dark:text-white/60"> — fucking dope</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://justfuckingusehttp.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-sm hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity underline"
            >justfuckingusehttp.com</a
          >
          <span class="text-sm text-black/60 dark:text-white/60"> — the OG shit</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://justfuckingusereact.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-sm hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity underline"
            >justfuckingusereact.com</a
          >
          <span class="text-sm text-black/60 dark:text-white/60">
            — for when you actually need it</span
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://justfuckingusecss.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-sm hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity underline"
            >justfuckingusecss.com</a
          >
          <span class="text-sm text-black/60 dark:text-white/60"> — stop fighting it, dipshit</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.justfuckinguserails.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-sm hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity underline"
            >justfuckinguserails.com</a
          >
          <span class="text-sm text-black/60 dark:text-white/60"> — Ruby motherfuckers unite</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mt-8 italic text-black/60 dark:text-white/60">
        Now stop reading and go fucking build something, asshole.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </Wrapper>
</BaseLayout>
